==English==
===Noun===
'''za'''

# An old [[solfeggio]] name for [[B flat]]; the seventh [[harmonic]], as heard in the [[aeolian]] [[string]]; so called by Tartini. It was long considered a false, but is the true note of the chord of the [[flat seventh]].

===Etymology 2===
From ''pizza,'' shortened.
===Noun===
#(''US slang, early 1980s'') [[pizza|Pizza.]]
'''Usage note:''' No longer used.

<!--Put translations, etc, under "pizza", unless you are aware of languages that have slang terms for "pizza"-->

{{webster}}

===Verb===
'''za'''
# To [[sort]] a list of words or names [[alphabetically]] backwards from Z to A. Derived from the buttons used in many [[computer]] [[program]]s to sort [[data]].

Antonym: [[az]]

